706712f-a.folder: Sheepshead Bay Road & Jerome Avenue, Brooklyn, NY
706712f-a.original_title: Brooklyn: Sheepshead Bay Road - Jerome Avenue
706712f-a.text:
(1)
Sheepshead Bay Road, north side, west of Jerome Ave., showing from fore to background the home of C.F. O'Neil (1890), the Island View Hotel (1890) and another hotel having no name which still stands in 1937. The Island View was demolished prior to 1929, and the other frame structure was modernized.

December 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2)
The same, sho ing Nos. 1503-1523 Sheepshead Bay Road, beyond is the Brighton Beach Line of the B.M.T. This hotel,not named,is at the N.W.
corner of East 16th Street.
January 1924.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

706713f-a.original_title: Brooklyn: Sheepshead Bay Road - Jerome Avenue
706713f-a.text:
Sheepshead Bay Road, east side, from and including Jerome Ave., to, but not including Voorhies Ave.  The view shows frame building at  Nos. 1601 to 1611 Sheepshead Bay Road.

July 8, 1933.

F.L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
